name: Boolean that specifies if continuous blood measurements are available.
The rate at which the blood was withdrawn from the subject.
Description of the type of tubing used, ideally including the material and (internal) diameter.
The length of the blood tubing, from the subject to the detector.
External dispersion time constant resulting from tubing.
Boolean that specifies if discrete blood measurements are available.
Measured haematocrit, i.e. the volume of erythrocytes divided by the volume of whole blood.
Boolean that specifies if metabolite measurements are available.
Boolean that specifies if plasma measurements are available.
Measured free fraction in plasma, i.e. concentration of free compound in plasma divided by total concentration of compound in plasma.
Method used to estimate free fraction.
